Ahhhhh!!\n< Serena >

Ohh...uh. So this is the feel of Venus's
beautiful princess... huh!\n< Man >
Ugh...hnnn...!\n< Serena >

I decided the moment I saw you. I
decided when Batbayar showed you off.\n< Man >
You were going to be mine.\n< Man >

I've always thought of doing this...!
Hnnn!!\n< Man >
Ahhhh!\n< Serena >
Hahaha! It took five years...!\n< Man >

Your, this place... is better than I
imagined! My interest is unending! My
blood won't settle down!\n< Man >

Are all women from the northern
territories like this?\n< Man >

This battle is almost over. The plains
will become one. Then, it's time to
ravage the empire's territory...\n< Man >

Next time, it might be interesting to
pass through the great forest and invade
the northern territories... eh!\n< Man >
Ah...ah...! Ugh...!\n< Serena >
Mo-mmy...\n< Child >
!!! You...! Why have you returned...!\n< Serena >

General. We've captured Batbayar's
brats.\n< Subordinate >

Good work. Hahaha. They're an ugly
bunch, nothing like their mother. Does
Batbayar's blood run strong in them?\n< Man >

Hmm... one is missing? There was a brash
older kid, wasn't there?\n< Man >
My apologies. They resisted.\n< Subordinate >
Ahhh...!\n< Serena >

If you haven't let them escape, it
doesn't matter.\n< Man >

After all, what we're going to do is the
same.\n< Man >
Then.\n< Subordinate >
Stop, stop it!\n< Serena >
Hmm--?\n< Man >
Please...! Spare the children...!\n< Serena >

They're not kids you wanted to have, are
they? A woman brought as spoils of
war...\n< Man >

The children are innocent... they're all
good kids...!\n< Serena >

The only light I've found in this
captive life...\n< Serena >

Mommy... why are you naked? Who is that
man?\n< Child >

This is...hnn! It's nothing... nothing
at all...!\n< Serena >
Mommy? Your face is red...\n< Child >

It's okay, it's all right...hnnk!
...That's why...!\n< Serena >

Hmph. Even if they're kids, you'd think
they'd be a bit sharper at that age.\n< Man >

Seems like the seed wasn't good. Or
maybe it's the education? You must have
doted on them.\n< Man >
Be quiet... be quiet...!\n< Serena >

Rest assured. My seed is of better
quality than Batbayar's. I'll make you
bear a replacement soon enough. A better
one.\n< Man >

If you're going to nurse anyway, it's
better to do so with a strong child born
from superior seed, right?\n< Man >
Take them away.\n< Man >
E-ji----!!!\n< Child >
Aaaa-----!!!!!!\n< Serena >

Now, now, don't cry. This is the way of
a chaotic world. The fate of the
steppes.\n< Man >
Ugh!\n< Serena >

A fine woman has the duty to bear
stronger children. It's her
responsibility.\n< Man >

Leaving behind weak seed is a sin
against our ancestors.\n< Man >

You...! How dare you...! How dare
you...!\n< Serena >

Hahaha, that's right, those eyes. The
eyes of a mother who has had her
children taken away. I wanted to see
those eyes!\n< Man >

I'll make a replacement for you soon
enough. You just need to keep bearing my
children.\n< Man >

Children of the man you hate. The
avengers of our children, the offspring.\n< Man >

They will be our children. They will
grow up smart and strong. Just imagining
them invading your homeland...\n< Man >

Makes my heart leap with excitement,
doesn't it? Hahaha, I'm looking forward
to it. I'm so looking forward to it...\n< Man >
